# Sidebar Layout Implementation Prompt

## When to Use Sidebar Layout
Use this layout for pages that need filtering, navigation, or additional controls:
- Search results pages
- Index pages with filters
- Pages with navigation menus
- Content that benefits from categorization

## Implementation Guidelines

### HTML Structure
```html
<div class="container">
    <div class="main-content"> <!-- Two-column layout -->
        <aside class="sidebar">
            <!-- Sidebar content -->
            <div class="filter-group-section">
                <h3 class="filter-section-heading">Filter Results</h3>
                <ul class="filter-options-list">
                    <li class="filter-option-item">Filter Item</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </aside>
        <main class="content-area">
            <h1 class="search-main-title">PAGE TITLE</h1>
            <!-- Main content here -->
        </main>
    </div>
</div>
```

### Sidebar Typography Hierarchy
- **Main Sidebar Title**: `.filter-section-heading` (first section) - `--fs-body-large` + bold
- **Section Titles**: `.filter-section-heading` - `--fs-body-small` + bold
- **Filter Items**: `.filter-option-item` - `--fs-body-small`
- **Compact Spacing**: Filter items use `0.25rem` padding for tight layout

### Layout Variants

#### Standard Sidebar (Default)
```html
<div class="main-content"> <!-- Standard width -->
```

#### Wide Sidebar (Optional)
```html
<div class="main-content wide"> <!-- Wider sidebar -->
```

### CSS Classes for Sidebar Content
```css
/* Sidebar sections */
.filter-group-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); /* Section spacing */
}

/* Main sidebar titles */
.filter-group-section:first-child .filter-section-heading {
    font-size: var(--fs-body-large);
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
}

/* Section titles */
.filter-section-heading {
    font-size: var(--fs-body-small);
    font-weight: bold;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
}

/* Filter items */
.filter-option-item {
    font-size: var(--fs-body-small);
    padding: 0.25rem 0; /* Compact spacing */
}
```

