## Best Practices
1. **Always check the style guide first**: Review `style-guide.html` for current design tokens
2. **Reference templates**: Use `shared/templates/` for proven layout patterns
3. Use semantic HTML (`<aside>`, `<main>`, `<section>`)
4. Follow the typography hierarchy for visual consistency
5. Use proper spacing variables (`--space-xl`, `--space-md`)
6. Implement responsive behavior for mobile devices
7. Test filter functionality and accessibility
8. Ensure theme compatibility (clean/terminal modes)
9. Keep filter items compact with `0.25rem` padding
10. Use `--fs-body-large` for main titles, `--fs-body-small` for sections